Part 10 – Why Clarity Functions Are Safer by Design

Clarity functions embody a different philosophy:

No reentrancy

No hidden loops

No gas surprises

No runtime ambiguity

This makes Clarity especially suitable for:

DeFi protocols

Identity systems

DAOs

Reputation and minting logic (like OnchainKMS)

Mastering Clarity functions means writing contracts that are boring in execution—but powerful in guarantees, which is exactly what blockchains need
